  "prompt": "How is Americium classified?",
  "response": "Americium is classified as a chemical element with the symbol Am and atomic number 95. It is part of the actinide series on the periodic table. As a transuranic element, it is not found naturally in the Earth's crust but is artificially produced, mainly through bombardment of plutonium. Americium is a radioactive metal and is primarily used in smoke detectors, as well as in some types of industrial gauges and radiographic equipment due to its alpha and gamma radiation emissions.",
